#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:11 b266d71dca1e4d50b1291ad04829dd37
msgid ""
"Mesh partitioning (or domain decomposition) is a fundamental "
"preprocessing step for parallel finite element analysis. The goal is to "
"divide the mesh into :math:`k` subdomains such that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:13 79b02d7d9e7143b4910c74fd1d488267
msgid "**Load Balance**: Each subdomain has roughly the same number of elements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:14 b0ecf29ffd064d8c89db5e73fbf8731d
msgid ""
"**Minimal Interface**: The number of shared nodes (communication cost) is"
" minimized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:16 e4b5886b40444a66a22dfcc3ad03c844
msgid ""
"TensorMesh provides a highly efficient, GPU-accelerated implementation of"
" **Recursive Spectral Bisection**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:19 6f3c194ea1ee41c98582ed8b30569b76
msgid "Algorithm Details"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:22 484b892aaa5348b7a186a9020d543287
msgid "Spectral Partitioning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:23 a4ec50dc283a4c0ab8d94a4ae41a19d0
msgid ""
"The method leverages the spectral properties of the **Graph Laplacian** "
"matrix :math:`L = D - A`, where :math:`A` is the adjacency matrix and "
":math:`D` is the degree matrix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:25 1fb6667f0e064e57b474aef2498ad9ec
msgid ""
"**Fiedler Vector**: The algorithm computes the eigenvector corresponding "
"to the second smallest eigenvalue of the Laplacian (known as the Fiedler "
"vector). This vector maps the graph vertices onto a line while preserving"
" locality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:26 c3a4044046844e5680938fda7817a3c2
msgid ""
"**Bisection**: Nodes are partitioned into two sets based on the median "
"value (or sign) of the Fiedler vector components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:27 7835988c8a644839b924ffed76b4301a
msgid ""
"**Recursion**: To partition into :math:`k=2^m` parts, the algorithm is "
"applied recursively to each subgraph."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:29 517b44fb18864923a0d8f6f7d97e3afe
msgid ""
"**GPU Acceleration** Solving the eigenvalue problem for large sparse "
"matrices is computationally intensive. TensorMesh utilizes "
"``torch.lobpcg`` (Locally Optimal Block Preconditioned Conjugate "
"Gradient) on the GPU to efficiently find the smallest eigenpairs of the "
"sparse Laplacian without moving data to the CPU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:33 0d735c803fef4df29ddbeda01b9c0c41
msgid "Ghost Nodes & Overlap"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:34 ca43d89000164a1183c76b53cfbcf7bf
msgid ""
"In element-based partitioning, elements are assigned to unique "
"partitions. However, nodes on the boundary (interface) must be shared "
"between partitions to maintain continuity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:36 e28b356a0d1540fbb32e66210b18b52b
msgid "**Internal Nodes**: Nodes belonging exclusively to one partition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:37 36f9f4958316442cb0f47dd46e6032d5
msgid "**Ghost Nodes**: Nodes shared by two or more partitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/examples/partition.rst:39 35c812efcf5742a784703f2046f1340e
msgid ""
"TensorMesh's ``partition_mesh`` function automatically handles this "
"topology. It returns a list of independent ``Mesh`` objects (submeshes). "
"Each submesh contains its own local nodes, but preserves the mapping to "
"the original mesh via the ``orig_nid`` (original node ID) point data. "
"This allows for easy data exchange during parallel computation."
msgstr ""

